import React, { useState } from 'react'; import Layout from '../components/Layout/Layout'; import './Admissions.css'; const Admissions = () => { const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState('process'); const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState({}); const toggleFAQ = (index) => { setIsOpen(prevState => ({ ...prevState, [index]: !prevState[index] })); }; const faqItems = [ { question: "What is the application deadline?", answer: "The application deadline for the upcoming academic year is March 1st. Late applications may be considered on a case-by-case basis." }, { question: "When will we receive the admission decision?", answer: "Admission decisions are typically sent out by April 15th. You will receive an email notification followed by an official letter." }, { question: "Are there any scholarships available?", answer: "Yes, we offer a variety of merit-based and need-based scholarships. Please visit the Financial Aid section for more details." }, { question: "Can we schedule a campus tour?", answer: "Absolutely! We encourage prospective students and their families to visit our campus. You can schedule a tour through our Visit Us page." } ]; return (
{/* Hero Section */}

Begin Your Educational Journey

Join our community of learners and discover your potential

{/* Admissions Tabs */}
{activeTab === 'process' && (

Admissions Process

Our admissions process is designed to help us get to know you and your potential to thrive in our school community.

1

Inquiry & Exploration

Submit an inquiry form, attend an open house, or schedule a campus tour to learn more about our school.

2

Application

Complete our online application form and submit all required documents by the deadline.

3

Assessment & Interview

Students may be required to complete an assessment, and families will participate in an interview with our admissions team.

4

Decision & Enrollment

Receive your admission decision and complete the enrollment process if accepted.

)} {activeTab === 'requirements' && (

Admissions Requirements

To ensure a complete application, please submit the following documents:

📝

Application Form

Complete our online application with accurate and current information.

📊

Academic Records

Official transcripts from the previous two years of schooling.

✉️

Recommendations

Two letters of recommendation from teachers or counselors.

📄

Personal Statement

A written essay or personal statement from the student.

)} {activeTab === 'dates' && (

Important Dates

Mark your calendar with these important admissions deadlines:

January 15

Application Opens

Begin submitting your applications for the next academic year.

March 1

Application Deadline

All applications and supporting materials must be submitted by this date.

March 15-30

Interviews

Schedule your family interview with the admissions committee.

April 15

Decision Notification

Admission decisions will be sent to all applicants.

May 1

Enrollment Deadline

Deadline for accepted students to confirm their enrollment.

)} {activeTab === 'financial' && (

Financial Aid & Scholarships

We believe in making quality education accessible. Explore our financial support options:

Merit-Based Scholarships

Awarded to students who demonstrate exceptional academic achievement, talent in arts or athletics, or leadership qualities.

Need-Based Financial Aid

Available to families who demonstrate financial need. Applications are reviewed confidentially by our financial aid committee.

Payment Plans

Flexible payment options are available to help families manage tuition costs throughout the academic year.

)}
{/* FAQ Section */}

Frequently Asked Questions

{faqItems.map((item, index) => (
{isOpen[index] &&
{item.answer}
}
))}
{/* Contact Section */}

Have More Questions?

Our admissions team is here to help you through the process.

Email

admissions@schoolname.edu

Phone

(123) 456-7890

Office Hours

Monday-Friday, 8:00 AM - 4:30 PM

 ); }; export default Admissions;
